text.text: I had such a great time lounging with the adorable kitties! You pay to get a certain amount of time in the kitty lounge + it comes with a free drink! The place is clean and well maintained for the kitties to roam around and enjoy. The staff was very kind and the overall vibe was super nice! Highly recommend coming here just to chill and help support an awesome business that helps cats in need! Please consider adopting, fostering and donating/helping your local shelters! ü©∑

Gatos and Beans were so helpful during the adoption of Abby and Alec! They were very attentive and answered all of my questions. This is a great cafe with an awesome mission. Even if you are not looking to adopt, stop by and grab a coffee to support!

Coffee and cats, what more could you ask for? The decor is great and all looks handmade, they are essentially a shelter where you can adopt the cats as well. Such a great mission and such a great way of accomplishing it. New favorite spot in Bham!

cafes.name: The Red Cat Coffeehouse @ Pepper Place

text.text: Trendy upscale coffee shop with a wide variety of beverages and some things to eat. Prices are somewhat high but to be expected from this type of establishment. I ordered the cold brew which was quite good. Ample seating indoors. There is also outdoor seating. Service was fast and staff were friendly.

First time here and definitely not my last. The staff provided great recommendations and great service. I had the Ham and Swiss Croissant & the Caramel Apple Spice Latte. They were both delicious! There were several seasonal drinks on the menu and a variety of breakfast items as well. I love the atmosphere as well with all the windows for the natural light to shine in and also the option of outdoor seating. This coffee shop was quite busy, but I understand why. I am adding The Red Cat to my list of favorite coffee shops in Birmingham. Great place to work or meet up with a friend!

My son took me to this coffee shop. We had mocha macchiato's and they were delicious. The upbeat music is a bit loud but pretty common. There were lots of students posted up with laptops open. The staff was friendly. They offer some food options but we only have coffee. What I loved to see is the diversity of the population in this coffee shop. The only thing I didn't really care for was all the smoke (from
the kitchen, I assume) in the shop.

Passed two Starbucks to get to this independently owned small business. But that was not the best part. The service was friendly and accurate and the taste of the coffee was excellent. They know how to use that big beautiful LaMarzocco for sure. Add to that the ambiance of the sitting area was welcoming and warm with decor that gave a nod to the history of the most important beverage goat ever helped many to uncover.  Well done on every level.

We were staying in a hotel nearby with rather limited and I ricy breakfast options.  What a treat it was to find the Red Cat.  Delicious food and coffee for every taste.  Unfortunately, they were out of grits the day we visited, so we didn't get to try their breakfast bowls, but the pastries were amazing.  The croissant for the sandwich was one of the best I had ever had.  Cold brew and lates, perfect.

My favorite coffee shop in all of Birmingham. The staff here make me feel welcome. The coffee is delicious and fast. Within a week of becoming a regular, everyone knew my name and my order. After getting my coffee, I often drive to work feeling such a pick-me-up, and I realize it‚Äôs not the caffeine, it‚Äôs from the love and kindness of all the staff making my morning a little brighter.

This was my 1st time trying the establishment. I ordered 3 Frappuccino caramel flavored drinks. It took about 10 to 15 minutes to receive my order, but the staff was so friendly, and the atmosphere was very pleasant. I would definitely try this location again, especially since they were helpful during a critical time of waiting for a family member to come out of surgery. I appreciate their service

I was scheduled for an appointment at UAB Highlands,  my appointment was on today which was wrong date Oct 14th, should be on 15th. I accidentally left my purse with money and credit cards at home rushing out door for transportation...which was waiting 30 minutes at my driveway..I jumped up out bed and rushed to car, after being told wrong date, I really wanted a cup of coffee,  after I've been a customer here several times, but never again!
I thought this company had a heart to serve, boy was I wrong!
I asked the heavy set white lady with dark hair and not a friendly face , , "Do you give courtesy cups, ? Her reply was, "what?"..I repeated my question.. her reply..."No we don't  sorry"
My God, it will cost you nothing to have compass! Not even a small light in her heart! Nothing! Boy I hope she doesn't have children,  I feel sorry for them if they're hungry!
Never get my money, nor my family's,  nor our congregations, nor my friend's business üíØ.
I have a business too, I will never treat a customer, a living soul like this person working here today did to me....my God.. not even a cup!!

Wasn‚Äôt acknowledged by staff who were standing in front of me having, what appeared to be, personal conversation. I asked to be helped. I ordered and got my drink but had to ask if they would give me my muffin. The wait person scowled , got my food, and didn‚Äôt acknowledge my saying thank you and continued scowling. Ugh. Plus, I had tipped when ordering. I should have waited. Food and coffee quite good though.

cafes.name: Cattyshack, Inc.
cafes.address: 2211 Seminole Dr SW Studio 1062, Huntsville, AL 35805, USA

text.text: Reserve a one hour time slot online to come hangout with a bunch of kittens and maybe even adopt one! It is $10 per person per hour and up to 12 people per session. Adoptions are $95 each. This place is always hopping it seems. It is located in the Lowe Mill arts and entertainment building which is very deceiving from the outside. Follow the directions in the reservation email to find the booth inside! The kittens are super friendly and love to play. Tons of room to just sit on the couch and let the cats come to you. We enjoyed our hour of cat loving. Will come again another day!
Our first time here and we LOVE IT!!! These cats made us so happy. Please come visit them.

We love going to Cattyshack and playing with the cats and kittens. It is always fun to see different cats everytime we have gone.  We love supporting this organization as we have 3 feral rescues at home and want all the cats to find their furever home.  Go play and maybe find the cat for you.

Chattanooga.name: Naughty Cat Cafe
Chattanooga.address: 3742 Tennessee Ave Suite 100, Chattanooga, TN 37409, USA

text.text:
What a wonderful experience !! They had approximately 40 cats in a couple of rooms. One room nicely decorated with couches and chairs and cat furniture. This room is a little dark on purpose. Fun to sit and let the cats come to you. There is a second room with full light and also lots of seating areas for cats and humans . Very clean! Amazingly friendly staff.
There are binders with all the cat information in case you like to adopt one.
Highly recommended activity to have fun and support a good cause!

We had never experienced a cat cafe before and I hope they are all as well done at the Naughty Cat Cafe! Several rooms full of cats to love on! Even a quiet room for the new residents to get used to their new lodgings. Highly recommend if you love cats. You will want to take them all home!

They have so many cats right now (12/13/2024)! All of them have so much personality and they‚Äôre sooooo soft! I came here with friends as a birthday gift to myself, I‚Äôm so glad I did. It is very calming sitting with the cats! They dim the lights and play soothing music while the cats just roam around. It is also extremely clean and the restroom smells great as well! They do provide binders all around the sitting area so you can learn about each cat, along with how to adopt one if you fall in love with one of the fur babies! As well as the cat petting, they provide you one free drink ‚Äî whether that be hot coffee, hot tea, soda, chocolate milk, or cold water! They also sell reasonably priced products, such as jewelry, cat toys, shot glasses, little pastries, and they even have cans of alcohol for sale (if that‚Äôs your thing!). I would 100% recommend this lovely place to anybody who even remotely enjoys cats! There are many different areas to sit, their one rule is to never pick up any of the cats.
Such a fun experience! The cats were so friendly and we really enjoyed spending time with them. The employee was very nice as well! Will definitely be coming back üôÇ

The perfect place to meet new friends, both human and feline. The sweetest Cats and kittens available for adoption are at this Catfe. I have adopted 2 and couldn't be happier with my choice. The Yoga classes are so good, and are tailored so every body can do them. The special events like the moon circles and tea rituals are so comforting and relaxing. There's also Kitty Kat story time and a room that's been designed for kids and families to enjoy with coloring books and a chalkboard. They also have a shop full of beautiful items. If that weren't enough they also do Birthday Parties and other special events!!!!

The yoga classes here are amazing. And they have different classes for different people! So everyone can take a class!

The special classes they offer have been SO COOL!
I‚Äôve done a cacao meditation class and some tea classes where you watch the tea bloom and just chill out with some awesome people. The vibe here is so cool and the way they are with helping the cats out is such a joy to see. They really do care about you and your needs as well as the cats. Highly recommend!

Loved my experience here! The store clerk was friendly and very personable. They had recently ‚Äúemployed‚Äù a storefront cat‚Äîa regularly visiting stray‚Äîwhen I visited.

There were adult cats and kittens a plenty! Lots of toys and spaces to use for interacting. Ample space to sit and chill or pet the babies. The space was really clean as well.

The fee is reasonable for an hour AND includes a coffee / tea that you can prepare for yourself.

I will definitely visit again when I‚Äôm in the area!

Staff very informative and helpful. She took care of the place and the cats. We ended up adopting a very cute loving playful kittey named Odette that we renamed Olivia. The setting was different than just an animal shelter. In a shelter they are all in cages. At this place they are all roaming free inside the house (designated room). You pay a small hourly fee to play and chill with all the cats there. Staff was top notch! Thank you Cat Cafe!

This is the cutest place! You can go and play with so many cats!  The adoption fee is very reasonable too, no matter if you're adopting a kitten or an older cat.  We got a new kitten for our family and he's the best!
Ordered the grilled chicken tender plate. Chicken had a nice flavor to it, and it was seasoned well. The fried Okra was very good too. I highly recommend this place, and great pricing to!

This is a good place to eat good food friendly service always check to see if you need anything I love eating there my favorite thing to eat is the BBQ sandwich with coleslaw on it and the fries are delicious I love it there good place good environment clean fast and friendly

The Best grilled chicken fingers around.  Mojos and coleslaw are really tasty also.   Must try if you‚Äôve never been here.  Will definitely recommend and will most definitely be back.   Go check them out

cafes.name: Kitty Kat Haven & Rescue
cafes.address: 3432 Old Columbiana Rd, Hoover, AL 35226, USA

text.text: Today I adopted the sweetest cat from Kitty Kat Haven. Brenda and the entire team was so kind and helpful. They care so well for the cats that come to them. Some of the negative reviews on here are very unfair. They are very clear about the expectations of adopting from them. Ensuring the cat‚Äôs safety is top priority (as it should be!) I cannot stress enough how kind and helpful the entire team was. I‚Äôm so grateful to them and I strongly recommend you come here if you are looking for you new furry baby!

Lovely place, great staff. You can drop by on weekends if you just want some kitty time. The "kitty kabin" in the back with all the "teenage" cats is the best place to just hang out and play with kitties. You'd be hard pressed not to walk out with one!
Very clean. Safe, loving space for the kitties. Hardworking, dedicated volunteers. Definitely check them out if you want to adopt, foster, or volunteer, or just spend some time with lots of kitties!
Favorite place to have a good time, great food, and great drinks while visiting my hometown...
Great Vibes

cafes.name: BuzzCatz Coffee & Sweets
cafes.address: 25689 Canal Rd Suite A, Orange Beach, AL 36561, USA

text.text: We ate here twice during our trip. The Buzzcat breakfast platter was delicious. I tried both the link sausage and the bacon, which were both perfectly cooked and very tasty.  The homemade whole wheat toast and the biscuits were to die for! The staff were very pleasant and did a great job. I would highly recommend this restaurant for a delicious breakfast!

Best place I visited on my vacation! The vibes are really cool and friendly and everything is clean. The kitten head biscuits were my favorite, light and easy to tear off and dip. Definitely add the preserves and gravy! Coffee was great. Highly recommend.
Best Mocha Frappe I've had! Fun, quirky atmosphere and good service! We stopped for the first time in 2018 and I remembered how delicious it was for this trip! Definitely a must in Orange Beach :)

Murfreesboro.name: Catfeine Cat Cafe
Murfreesboro.address: 517 Cason Ln D, Murfreesboro, TN 37128, USA

text.text: This place was a really sweet experience and IMMACULATE to boot. I wasn't sure what to expect but its such a humane way to provide an opportunity for cats to be fostered/adopted. The owner Taura is very kind and is very involved in the process and makes sure the cats are cared for. I have NEVER been in a cleaner environment with that many animals, anywhere!! The vibe was laid back, comfortable and you would not know there were 20 cats there. You could tell they were comfortable and cared for in that environment. Those cats aren't just fosters to that business, they're family. I would give more stars if I could!!!!!
Absolutely love this place, the environment was very friendly, the staff was super welcoming and the cats well they were really energetic today lol. Took some silly photos of the cats

You have cat to be kitten me right meow!!! This place is everything a cat and coffee lover wants. The cats here are all so sweet and well taken care of. I set up my laptop and worked for a couple hours while the kitties played around me. I wish I could adopt them all!!!

cafes.name: Kitty's Kafe
cafes.address: 3800 Gulf Shores Pkwy #100, Gulf Shores, AL 36542, USA

text.text: Excellent selection of Eggs Benedict!  I love this restaurant!  Friendly and fast service in an awesome environment!  Delicious breakfast taters!

Hidden Gem should be the title.
Italian so good that if the lights were dimmer, you could easily imagine a fat mafia boss in the corner... yet this place is family friendly.
Food in pictures is about $15 bucks. So you don't need to be able to afford an Armani suit and some fat gold rings to try the joint.
Does live music sometimes.

The breakfast and lunch here is very good!... This is one of those places you go to expecting great service and food.  I've had a simple eggs, bacon and sausage breakfast(very good) many times. However, The Debris Po Boy sandwich was very good for lunch.  Stop by if you want great service along with excellent country valued cuisine.
